I have lived in this country for right around 20 years. My family settled in the US due to its abundance of economic opportunity and its open mind. Just in my time alive, I have witnessed a pandemic, a reality TV star become president, multiple economic depressions, endless wars, and the rent seeking behavior of society.

Through real world experience, I have gotten to understand in painful detail the strengths and weaknesses of this land of 50 states bound by a piece of paper. Here is the biggest issue America faces right now:

**Every problem is considered an unprecedented problem**

That's it. Seriously. 

There is a war somewhere in the world? No worries, our army will fix it!
You are sick? No worries, take this cheap pill and you will be great again!
Are you hungry? Forget about cooking yourself, eat this Big Mac instead!
You want money? Forget about working, just open a Polymarket account instead!

When you treat every issue like this, it necessitates a need for immediate solutions. If the silver bullet will take a long time to hit its target, then naturally a market opens up for cheap and easy solutions.

Cheap and easy solutions never fix the root issue but it gives the impression that it does, so now no one actually wants to fix the root cause.

The scary thing about cheap solutions is that it oftentimes does work for a moment. This feeds our evolved brains to abandon long term thinking for short term gain and profit. Why solve the underlying issue when you can profit off of it?

So seriously America, that one extra cheap pill that you take is not going to make you healthy forever. Structural issues take time and pain to resolve, that's how the universe works. 

Learn to suffer and fix the root causes, please. This is so ridiculous.
